Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharpish turn. Clay fine light brown; red-brown core; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with large star symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 27a, 24 Name Aristeidas. From same die as Alexandria Museum, ALEX ABC 0032.36; re-cutting more obvious on this piece, but both show extra ou at end of line 1.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0613)
